{
  "texts": [
    "The top three teams were as accurate as the human raters on average across all ten scored items-they used completely different methods but yielded a high average QWK (> 0.93).",
    "There was no bias in any of the major demographic groups.",
    "However, it should be noted that the investigation of subgroup bias ended with SMDs, and no additional detection methods were used to detect different types of unfairness.",
    "Automated scoring is not at all a new capability in educational assessment, with the first systems created in the 1960s.",
    "These earlier systems were not based on AI, per se, but on supervised models built by NLP scientists using feature sets that were somewhat explainable."
  ]
}